This paper deals with the classification of image datasets using Deep Neural Networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theory of Vapnik-Chervonenkis dimension, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of texture features and hand-crafted feature extraction is also a common topic in computer vision and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the VC dimension of neural networks, which is a topic in neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of intrinsic dimension, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
